-- Inter Milan Defeats Congo's TP Mazembe 3-0 to Claim FIFA's Club World Cup
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2010-12-18T18:56:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-18/inter-milan-defeats-tp-mazembe-3-0-in-final-of-fifa-club-world-cup.html
Inter Milan defeated TP Mazembe
Englebert 3-0 in the final of the FIFA Club World Cup in Abu
Dhabi.  Goran Pandev, Samuel Eto’o and Jonathan Biabiany scored for
Inter, which is the fourth consecutive European team to win the
tournament contested by the champions of the continental soccer
federations. TP Mazembe of Congo was the first African team to
reach the title match in the tournament’s 10-year history.  Sporting Club Internacional of Brazil defeated South
Korea’s Seongnam Ilhwa 4-2 in the third-place game.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  